HEADWORD: Shastra
<hw>Shas"tra</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Skr. <ets>c⟦amac⟧stra</ets> an
order or command, a sacred book, fr. <ets>c⟦amac⟧s</ets> to order,
instruct, govern. Cf. <er>Sastra</er>.]</ety> <def>A treatise for
authoritative instruction among the Hindoos; a book of institutes;
especially, a treatise explaining the Vedas.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>sastra</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

